Find the max element in an array:

23	65	12	87	12	343	098	12	76	312


PRE-CONDITION:
●	To get an array int  array [] = [values].
●	We need to define two variable (int i max). 
●	To get the min in an array to consider as max value (max=array[0]).
●	Initialise =1 and max=0.
●	Increment the i using(++).
●	Compare the max value <array[i] then store the  max=array[i].
POST-CONDITION:
●	After the loop termination the value of the max is print.

LOOP-VARIANT:
●	The loop should terminate the value of the max must be compare the   others values i <=n.
●	In other words loops should not terminate until we have n compare to max. 
LOOP-INVARIANT:
●	You need to set the loop invariant to ensure correct output after the loop termination.
●	Loop invariant must be true before and after each iteration.
●	Before ith iteration of the loop variable max is equal to (max=array[i]) 1 to i-1.
●	After the ith iteration variable max is equal to 1 to i.

PSEUDEOCODE:
1.	 START
2.	 INITIALIZE arr[] = {25, 11, 7, 75, 56}
3.	 max = arr[0]
4.	 REPEAT STEP 5 for(i=0; i< arr.length; i++)
5.	 if(arr[i]>max) max=arr[i]
6.	 PRINT "Largest element in given array:"
7.	 PRINT max
8.	 END


