Move all zero end of array:
PRE-CONDITON:
●	To get the array variables and arry values{ }.
●	To initialise the two variables (int nz++,z++).
●	To check in the while loop (nz<len).
●	if statement to be compare(if(num[nz]!=0)).
●	To increment the values (nz++,z++)
●	Other wise else part will be print.
POST-CONDITION:
●	After the loop terminte output will be print in num as array format.

LOOP-VARIANT:
●	After the loop terminate if is not satisfied else part will be print.
LOOP-INVARIANT:
●	You need to set the loop invariant to ensure correct output after the loop termination.
●	Loop invariant must be true before and after each iteration.

PSEUDOCODE:
1.START
2.INITILIZE arr[]={2,3,0,6,0,6};
3.INITIALIZE VARIABLES int nz=0,z=0;
4.LOOP while(nz<len)
5.STATEMENT if(num[nz]!=0)
6,INCREMENT nz++,z++;
7.ELSE
8.nz++;
9.PRINT STATEMENT
10.END



